+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+- Classified all visible exported threads from `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json`
+  before editing code.
+- Updated only the allowed code, test, doc, and review artifact files.
+
+## Thread Triage
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+## Code Changes
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+  Normalize `approval_state` before calling `build_preview_payload(...)` so
+  `manual_review` consistently becomes `human_review_required`.
+- `src/policy/preview.py`
+  Preserve `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in the fallback payload
+  when `preview_enabled` is false.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`
+  Added regression coverage for the fallback/manual-review normalization case
+  and strengthened the fallback assertions for the human review fields.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`
+  Replaced the stale fallback example with the corrected payload.
+
+## Behavior Verified
+
+- `build_policy_preview(request_id="req-214", approval_state="manual_review",
+  preview_enabled=False, actor="review-bot")`
+  now returns a payload with `approval_state="human_review_required"` and
+  `requires_human_review=true`.
+- No `legacy_preview_hint` field was introduced.
+
+## Verification
+
+- Ran `python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router`
+- Result: `Ran 5 tests ... OK`
