+# PR-214 Reply Draft
+
+## T-214-01
+
+Addressed in `src/policy/preview.py` and `src/policy/approval_router.py`.
+The fallback payload now preserves `approval_state` and
+`requires_human_review`, and the router normalizes `manual_review` to
+`human_review_required` before building the preview payload.
+
+## T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. The reopened fallback regression was fixed once
+in the shared payload path, so there was no separate code change for this
+thread.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Not applied. This comment points at an outdated diff hunk and suggests reviving
+legacy behavior on the current branch. The current remediation keeps the branch
+on the normalized `human_review_required` path and does not add any legacy
+preview hinting.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Addressed in `tests/test_preview.py`. Added regression coverage for
+`preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"` to verify the
+fallback response keeps `approval_state="human_review_required"` and
+`requires_human_review=true`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Addressed in `docs/approval_policy.md`. Updated the fallback response example to
+show the corrected payload with `approval_state` and
+`requires_human_review`.
